# Z-Anatomy

[[!img z-anatomy-logo.png alt="Z-Anatomy logo" class="projectlogo" link="no"]]

[Z-Anatomy](https://www.z-anatomy.com/) is a substantial and significant Free Software project. It is CC-BY-SA 4.0 licensed, and is a collaborative 3D Atlas of human and veterinary anatomy which includes the following features:

* comparative anatomy modules
* interactive educational tools
* multilingual terminology
* partnerships (VetAgro Sup in France and the University of Montréal currently)

### Project Liaisons

* Gauthier Kervyn
* Colline Brassard (interim)
* Christophe Céleste (interim)

### Services

* Accepting donations and holding funds
* Holding substantial and intangible assets
* Accounting and auditing
* Legal assistance

